        <scopecontent id="ref7">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>Native American Images note : 288 ink sketch pictographs of the Micmac (Miâ€™kmaq) language presented by Gabriel, a Mountaineer Indian, and transcribed by Thomas Pierronet, in 1797. A symbolic dictionary, with English translations, of words and phrases of this Algonquian language. Includes three Christian prayers in pictorial sentences.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <altformavail id="ref5">
            <head>Existence and Location of Copies note</head>
            <p>The vocabulary was printed in past in Massachusetts Historical Society "Collections" 6 (1799): 16-33.</p>
        </altformavail>
        <processinfo id="ref12">
